Hind
wings well developed.

Aedeagus (
Figs. 12–19
) stout; AeL 0.38 mm ; median lobe with separate ventral and dorsal apical portions; internal armature strongly asymmetrical, composed of several complicated darkly sclerotized components, including two bunches of needle-like sclerites well-visible in lateral view; parameres slender and with 2–4 apical setae of various lengths.

Distribution. South Australia (
Fig. 20
) and Victoria (see Remarks).
